  "text": "The API key authentication in Grafana follows this flow: (1) **ContextHandler middleware** (`pkg/services/contexthandler/contexthandler.go`) intercepts all HTTP requests and calls `authenticator.Authenticate()` to identify the caller. (2) The **authn registration** (`pkg/services/authn/authnimpl/registration.go`) registers the API key client via `clients.ProvideAPIKey()`. (3) The **API key authn client** (`pkg/services/authn/clients/api_key.go`) is the core implementation \u2014 it extracts the token from the Authorization header, decodes it (supporting both modern `gl`-prefixed tokens via `satokengen` and legacy base64 tokens via `apikeygen`), retrieves the key from the database, and validates it via `validateApiKey()` which checks: expiration (`key.Expires`), revocation (`key.IsRevoked`), org membership, and service account binding. (4) The **apikey model** (`pkg/services/apikey/model.go`) defines the `APIKey` struct with `Expires`, `IsRevoked`, `Role`, and `ServiceAccountId` fields. (5) The **apikey service** (`pkg/services/apikey/apikey.go` + `apikeyimpl/apikey.go`) provides the service interface and implementation. (6) The **xorm store** (`pkg/services/apikey/apikeyimpl/xorm_store.go`) handles DB operations including `GetAPIKeyByHash` and `AddAPIKey` (which computes expiration from `SecondsToLive`). (7) **Token generation/decoding** is handled by `pkg/components/satokengen/tokengen.go` (modern prefixed keys) and `pkg/components/apikeygen/apikeygen.go` (legacy keys). (8) For gRPC, a separate **interceptor** (`pkg/services/grpcserver/interceptors/auth.go`) also authenticates API keys and enforces role-based scope (requiring admin role).",
